      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "began to be sore amazed",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] “To drede,” Wyclif. We have already met this word in ch. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Mark 9:15",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", where it was applied to the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "amazement",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " of the people when they saw the Lord after the Transfiguration, and we shall meet with it again in ch. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Mark 16:5-6",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", where it is applied to the holy women at the Sepulchre. St Mark alone applies the word to our Lord’s sensations at this crisis of His life.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
