            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "to be very heavy",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] “to heuye,” Wyclif. The original word thus translated only occurs (1) here, (2) in the parallel, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 26:37",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", and (3) in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Php 2:26",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", “for he (Epaphroditus) longed after you all, and was ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "full of heaviness",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".” Buttmann suggests that the root idea is that of being “",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "away from home",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ",” and so “confused,” “beside oneself.” Others consider the primary idea to be that of “loathing” and “discontent.” Truly in respect to His human nature our Lord was ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "far from home",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", far from His native skies, and the word may be taken to describe the awfulness of His isolation, unsupported by a particle of human sympathy,—a troubled, restless state, accompanied by the keenest mental distress.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
